# Fresh codebase on every prompt

Cursor indexes the repo automatically. You must still **re-read and search** on every user message.

## Required

1. Search/read the codebase for the user's topic before answering
2. Before edits, scan related modules and entry points
3. After you edit files, re-read them before claiming success
4. After git pull or branch change, invalidate all prior assumptions

## Never

- Answer architecture questions from memory without checking files
- Assume file contents match an earlier chat message
- Skip exploration because you "already looked at this"
